sql:
SELECT customer_id, COUNT(*)
FROM policies
GROUP BY customer_id;

external_knowledge:
- "folks" refers to customers; 
- "basic coverage types" refers to the type of policy;
- "incidents they've reported" refers to claims made by the customer;
- "timeline for a particular kind of insurance" specifies the date range and policy type for which claims are being counted.

- "Golden touch" refers to customers with a credit score above 700;
- "Call California their home" means customers whose addresses include 'California';
- "Storm clouds" metaphorically refers to the number of claims.

